metadata.name: The Gaze
metadata.description: Waking up in the darkness, he felt it. The gaze. No, it's not him looking into the screens at all those faces anymore: it's the faces looking at him. Into him. It was no use going outside, the people glued to the screens doing exactly what the other faces on the screens were telling them. It was quiet, and you could hear the leaves falling. Nature had never seemed so weak to him.
